                            <comment id="17732530" author="garydgregory" created="Wed, 14 Jun 2023 13:08:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=uhafner&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;uhafner&quot;&gt;uhafner&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you for your report.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you look at git master now, you&apos;ll find two new passing tests:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    @Test
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void testIo803StringReaderSanityCheck() {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; StringReader reader = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; StringReader(&quot;&quot;);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; InputSource inputSource = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; InputSource(reader);
        assertThrows(SAXException.class, () -&amp;gt; DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance().newDocumentBuilder().parse(inputSource));
    }

    @Test
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void testIo803SAXException() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; IOException {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; StringReader reader = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; StringReader(&quot;&quot;);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; ReaderInputStream inputStream = ReaderInputStream.builder().setCharset(StandardCharsets.UTF_8).setReader(reader).get()) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; InputSource inputSource = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; InputSource(inputStream);
            assertThrows(SAXException.class, () -&amp;gt; DocumentBuilderFactory.newInstance().newDocumentBuilder().parse(inputSource));
        }
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would you try to reproduce your issue in a test based only on Commons IO? You can attach it here, comment on it here, or provide it as a PR.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17732716" author="JIRAUSER300882" created="Wed, 14 Jun 2023 19:32:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Interesting, I&apos;ll try to dig into that a little bit deeper on the weekend!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17732858" author="JIRAUSER300882" created="Thu, 15 Jun 2023 05:53:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can it be, that the issue has been resolved in main since 2.13.0? There are a couple of commits in that area (I did&apos;t try to bisect).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I run my tests (see link above) against 2.13.0 I get an &lt;tt&gt;IllegalStateException&lt;/tt&gt;, when I run the tests against 2.14.0-SNAPSHOT (main) I correctly get a &lt;tt&gt;SAXParseException&lt;/tt&gt;.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I think we can close this issue when 2.14.0. (or 2.13.1) is released! Thanks anyway!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17732988" author="garydgregory" created="Thu, 15 Jun 2023 10:38:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Quite possible indeed as the tests show &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
